annotation.TEXT: Alright. Let's resume the game now, and begin 0-1-2!

Dying also resets the B blocks, BTW. Well, since I died, I guess I'm not going to worry about getting every star on this run. Also, I'm not going to do a "Demo count" for this game, since I may cut out future failures.
Next time, 0-1-3! To be continued... Ze!
WARNING: Do not press Esc if you want to pause! The Esc key instantly closes the game! Instead, it's the Enter key that pauses this game. (Why was it made that way?)
There's more well-hidden stars to the upper-left here, but I've gotta time this jump just right as the B effect is ending...
Okay, here's me showing that I can peg the mole FOEs the instant that they emerge from the dirt. (Remember that last time, they seemed to be immune to my orbs for a moment after they emerged.)
D'oh. Not fast enough. Umm... Is there a reset pipe around here?
For one thing, replays work now, and I've got a replay to show off here. It's of me 100%-ing 0-1-1.
Whoops. Missed the B there. Well, that only cost me a couple seconds.
Made it that time. I'd better be careful, since I've only got two lives left.
And then, after the replay ends, I'm back at the title screen. Okay, give me a moment here...
Bah. I'm not gonna be fast enough. Can I reset this one using the pipe back here?

BTW, there are no 1-ups in this game. If you get a bigger combo than that, I think every hit starting with the 9th is worth 10000 points. However, you always start each level with a fresh 5 lives, regardless of any previous deaths.
I see those stars over there, which would've been blocked off if I had hit that B too soon.
Yeah, I was able to find all 100 stars on my own without much trouble this time. However, the tricky part was getting them all without dying.
Nuts. I wasn't fast enough, but there's another reset pipe, fortunately.
GOOOOOAAAAALLLLL!!!!!
No. Oh, wait! I saw something in the upper-left here!
Yep, I just drill stomped a bullet there, which added 250 to my score.
There's a couple above the first Chuck FOE's starting position, and I'll point them out when I get to them.
I'll be coming back for that B in a moment.
Just made it, and what's this? Yeah, levels can have multiple midpoints, so this level isn't actually that short.
Alright, what's up next? ...Oh, boy.
Duck jumping is possible in this game, BTW.
Well, obviously, I'm going to want to give that another go.
Doesn't look like it, and uhh... I think I'm stuck now. Well, that just happened. Fortunately, the pause menu has the usual options, including "Give up and Retry", which starts the level over.
15 attempts later...
"Perfect!!" Also, in case you were wondering, for the normal score bonuses above: "Marisa" = Lives remaining x 10000. "Starts" = (Stars collected)² x 10. "Time" = Seconds left x 100.
Wow, those two stars were well-hidden.
So, a midpoint already? This level's kinda short. Anyway, just like in most Mario games, you can run across one-tile gaps in this game.
NOOOOO!!!!! Well, that was a demo, to show you guys what happens if you die.
Awesome combo! (8 hits)
Ah, yep! There were the 4 other stars I was missing!
Shoot! I was so close, too!
Use drill stomps for greater landing accuracy.
Bush!
However, I didn't actually want to hit that B block yet, due to the stars. Also, once a B block is hit, it can't be activated again, unless you go through a pipe to reset the area.
No, I'm not going to preserve this replay.
Thanks, dude! Here, have a hammer orb. Okay, I'm going to go to ludicrous speed for a moment...
Wow. Just made it. This is the only way that I've found to reach these three low stars here and still stay alive.
Ha. I remembered not to jump right into the suddenly-appearing guy above me here this time!
Hey there, big guy. Now look up in the air over here, and you'll see two stars up there, which I missed last time. However, I can't jump high enough to reach them, unless I get a boost...
Alright, so there's the demonstration of how going through a pipe resets the B blocks. Also, while this reset the B blocks, the current activation was still in effect.
Okay, now for the stars that I missed last time...
Looks like I'll need to do this part without the B in effect to get those stars below. Also, watch out for the attacks from above here.
Don't forget about the 2 well-hidden stars up here, of course.

Yeah, I'll preserve this replay. Now, nathanisbored did inform me that replays in this game can desync, especially with RNG-based enemies such as Chain Chomps later on. That's why I recorded this run live.
Alright, I'm nearing the end of the level, where the remaining stars I missed are.
This level introduces something new, the B block, which I'll get to in a moment. First, is there anything hidden above that rocky structure to the left?
Pfft. That's a fail. I was intending to use that section's reset pipe to get another shot at the section I'm currently working on.
Alright, let's run, run, run!
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World. As nathanisbored suggested, I have now updated to Version 1.05, which fixes a few things.
Oh, I think in the process of updating to 1.05, the mole FOEs were adjusted to be vulnerable to my orbs the instant that they emerge from the dirt. I'll show that off a bit more later.
Last life! Don't screw it up!
Made it! Alright, I managed to avoid Game Over!
Just showing that I can drill stomp the Venus Fire Trap FOE.
Unfortunately, I still let the moles get me.
I did rather poorly, though...
Alright, here we are. Now, nathanisbored mentioned that there were some stars above these bricks. But, how do I get on top of them? Well, Mr. Chuck FOE over here could be of assistance...

Unfortunately, I'm still getting lag, even if I'm not recording with HyperCam 2, which is odd, since I can play the regular Touhou games all the way up to 15 with no lag on this PC, and Super Marisa World is about 8 years old now.
Well, not down that pit. That's for sure.
Made it! And, from here, I can just go over the top of the rest of the level to reach Koakuma!
Anyway, the B block toggles these green blocks from non-solid to solid, and vice versa. This lasts for 10 seconds, and you can see how much time remains by looking at the counters on the blocks.
That's interesting how the Chuck FOE can break bricks by hitting them from below. Anyway, that is all 100 stars, so I am done with this level!
Okay, for the next part, I've really gotta go fast here!
